### TITLE ###
RecursiveLambdaSelfCallResolves
### DESCRIPTION ###
A lambda bound to a local that calls itself recursively. The
pre-plant places a Never-return placeholder on the symbol BEFORE
synth'ing the body, so the recursive call inside resolves to a
TypingFnT (with Never return) instead of Dynamic. The recursive
return contributes Never, drops in union, and the base case
determines the inferred return.
### INPUT ###
fact = fn(n: int):
    if n <= 1:
        return 1
    return fact(n - 1) * n
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  fact @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  n @ 2:8 -> int
  fact @ 4:12 -> fn(int) -> never
  n @ 4:17 -> int
  n @ 4:26 -> int

# Symbol types
  fact (local): fn(int) -> int
  n (param): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
RecursiveLambdaPureLoopDynamic
### DESCRIPTION ###
All return paths recursive - no concrete return type to pin.
Inferred as Dynamic, same fallback used for purely recursive
hoisted fns.
### INPUT ###
loop = fn(x: int):
    return loop(x + 1)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  loop @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  loop @ 2:12 -> fn(int) -> never
  x @ 2:17 -> int

# Symbol types
  loop (local): fn(int) -> dynamic
  x (param): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
RecursiveLambdaMultiPathUnioned
### DESCRIPTION ###
Two non-recursive base paths return int and str; the recursive
arm drops as Never. Inferred return is int|str.
### INPUT ###
pick = fn(x: int):
    if x < 0:
        return "neg"
    if x == 0:
        return 0
    return pick(x - 1)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  pick @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  x @ 2:8 -> int
  x @ 4:8 -> int
  pick @ 6:12 -> fn(int) -> never
  x @ 6:17 -> int

# Symbol types
  pick (local): fn(int) -> str|int
  x (param): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
RecursiveLambdaCallFromOutsideUsesInferredReturn
### DESCRIPTION ###
Outside the lambda, the recursive lambda's symbol now carries
the finalized TypingFnT (real return), so a call from main scope
gets the inferred return, not Dynamic.
### INPUT ###
fact = fn(n: int):
    if n <= 1:
        return 1
    return fact(n - 1) * n

result = fact(5)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  fact @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  n @ 2:8 -> int
  fact @ 4:12 -> fn(int) -> never
  n @ 4:17 -> int
  n @ 4:26 -> int
  result @ 6:1 -> <no-type>
  fact @ 6:10 -> fn(int) -> int

# Symbol types
  fact (local): fn(int) -> int
  n (param): int
  result (local): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
TypedLambdaRecursiveCallUsesDeclared
### DESCRIPTION ###
When the user declares the type at the binding site, the
declared TypingFnT was already on the symbol via sym.Declared.
The recursive call sees that directly - no placeholder needed.
### INPUT ###
fact: fn(int) -> int = fn(n: int):
    if n <= 1:
        return 1
    return fact(n - 1) * n
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  fact @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  n @ 2:8 -> int
  fact @ 4:12 -> fn(int) -> int
  n @ 4:17 -> int
  n @ 4:26 -> int

# Symbol types
  fact (local): fn(int) -> int
  n (param): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
